  "slug": "smithee",
  "title": "Smithee",
  "description": "Combine all the parts",
  "body": "<center>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 36px;\">Smithee</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000; font-size: 36px;\">HEADS UP</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000; font-size: 24px;\">This mod is still in development, which could potentially lead to unwanted results.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 24px;\">Smithee is a mod all about different tool-part combinations. Its goal is not to be a clone of <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/tinkers-construct\">Tinker's Construct</a>, but rather a \"spiritual successor\" with high customizability.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 18px;\">You can add new custom tool materials and change their stats all via configs.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 150px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 24px;\"><img src=\"https://media.forgecdn.net/attachments/329/306/java_vteqyoacik.png\" /></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 24px;\">The 3 different tool stations:</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 24px;\">- Disassembly Table - Breaks apart the tools back to their original components</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 24px;\">- Assembly Table - Combines tool parts into tools. Also used for embossing</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 24px;\">- Chiseling Table - Chisel materials into tool parts (requires a chisel)</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 24px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The items in the inventory are embossments used for giving additional stats to tools. You can only add 1 embossment per tool level, which is acquired by shift-right-clicking with the tool, which exchanges your XP for tool XP.</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 360px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 24px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><img src=\"https://media.forgecdn.net/attachments/329/305/java_twhunyh60x.png\" /></span></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 24px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Currently supports materials from the following mods:</span></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 18px;\">- <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/astromine-foundations/files\">Astromine Foundations</a></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 18px;\">- <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/mythicmetals\">Mythic Metals</a></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 18px;\">- <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/oh-the-biomes-youll-go-fabric\">BiomesYouGo</a></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 18px;\">- <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/diamold\">Diamold</a></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 18px;\">- <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/betternether\">Better Nether</a></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 18px;\">- <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/betterend\">Better End</a></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Join the <a href=\"https://discord.gg/vMjzgS4\">Development Discord</a> if you want to help out or follow progress.</span><br /></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 24px;\">Any help is appreciated (be it code, stat-balancing, ideas/suggestions, etc.)</span></p>\n</center>",
